This repository is a fork of the original QuietCool Whole House Attic Fan ESPHome
component created by thadd (https://codeberg.org/thadd/quietcool-house-fan), which
itself builds on protocol reverse-engineering work by Caleb Crome
(https://github.com/ccrome/quiet-cool-rf-remote). Full credit for the original
implementation, protocol analysis, and transmit-side design belongs to those authors.
This fork adds remote-receive/decode functionality on top of that original work. The
upstream repository does not publish a license; this MIT license applies to this fork
and its modifications, offered in the same spirit of open sharing as the upstream
project. If the original author wishes to specify different terms for the code they
contributed, please open an issue and this file will be updated accordingly.

